# AlgoMaster Online Judge

AlgoMaster Online Judge is a multi-tenant, multi-role competitive programming platform designed for educational institutions. It supports secure sandboxed evaluation of 6 programming languages (C/C++/Java/Python/Go/JavaScript), providing a complete online programming teaching and competition experience for students, teachers, and administrators.

## Architecture Overview

```
┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐
│                  │     │              Backend (Rust)              │     │                 │
│    Frontend      │     │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐    │     │  Judge Worker   │
│  React + Vite    │────>│  │           API (Axum)            │    │     │  Redis Streams  │
│  TypeScript      │     │  │  11 domain crates + api-infra   │    │<────│  cgroups/seccomp│
│  Port 5173 / 80  │     │  │  PostgreSQL + Redis + WebSocket │    │     │  Compile / Exec │
│                  │     │  └─────────────────────────────────┘    │     │  Sandbox        │
└──────────────────┘     │                 Port 3000               │     └─────────────────┘
                         └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                    ▲                    ▲
                                    │                    │
                              PostgreSQL 16          Redis 7
                                    ▲
                                    │
                         ┌─────────────────────┐
                         │  Feature Gateway    │
                         │  Port 3001          │
                         └─────────────────────┘
```

**Core Data Flow:** Users submit code through the frontend, which is sent to the API server. The API publishes evaluation tasks to Redis Streams, where judge workers consume tasks, compile and execute code in a Linux sandbox, and callback results to the API. The API then pushes results to the frontend in real-time via WebSocket. The Feature Gateway provides dynamic feature flag resolution for the platform.

## Core Features

- **6 Programming Languages** — C, C++, Java, Python, Go, JavaScript, covering mainstream teaching and competition scenarios
- **Sandboxed Execution** — Three-layer sandbox mechanism based on cgroups (memory/CPU limits), chroot (filesystem isolation), and seccomp (system call filtering) to ensure evaluation isolation and security
- **Multi-Tenant Multi-Role** — Supports multi-school/multi-campus independent operations with built-in student, teacher, admin, root four-level RBAC permission system, strict data isolation by tenant
- **Real-time Evaluation Feedback** — WebSocket pushes evaluation progress, leaderboard updates, contest status, and instant notifications
- **Contest System** — Create contests, assign problems, real-time leaderboards, contest chat rooms
- **Classes & Assignments** — Teachers can create classes, manage students, publish assignments, view student submission reports
- **Discussion & Blog** — Problem discussion area, technical blog, comment system to build a learning community
- **Code Plagiarism Detection** — Similarity-based plagiarism detection module with admin backend configuration
- **Private Messaging** — Real-time private messages between users with unread message notifications
- **Full-text Search** — Search problems, users, discussions, blogs and other content
- **Import/Export** — Batch import/export of problems for problem bank management and migration
- **Feature Gateway** — Dynamic feature flag system for enabling/disabling platform capabilities

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Frontend Framework | React + TypeScript + Vite | React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Vite 7 |
| UI Components | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn + Lucide Icons | — |
| State Management | Zustand (client) + TanStack React Query (server) | — |
| Form Validation | react-hook-form + Zod | — |
| Code Editor | Monaco Editor (code submission) + CodeMirror (Markdown editing) | — |
| API Server | Rust + Axum + SQLx | Rust Edition 2021, Axum 0.7, SQLx 0.8 |
| Judge Worker | Rust + Redis Streams + cgroups/seccomp | Rust Edition 2021 |
| Feature Gateway | Rust + Axum | Rust Edition 2021 |
| Database | PostgreSQL | 16 |
| Cache / Message Queue | Redis | 7 |
| Container Orchestration | Docker Compose | — |

