## Quick Start

For detailed installation and configuration guide, see [GETTING-STARTED.md](GETTING-STARTED.md).

### Docker Full-Stack Deployment

```bash
docker compose up -d --build
```

Initialize with demo data:

```bash
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/online_judge \
  ./scripts/bootstrap_demo.sh
```

Access URLs:

| Service | URL |
|---------|-----|
| Frontend | `http://localhost:5173` |
| API | `http://localhost:3000` |
| Feature Gateway | `http://localhost:3001` |
| Health Check | `http://localhost:3000/health` |

### Local Development

**1. Start infrastructure:**

```bash
docker compose up -d postgres redis
```

**2. Start API server:**

```bash
cd backend/api
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/online_judge \
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379 \
JWT_SECRET=dev-secret \
FEATURE_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:3001 \
cargo run
```

**3. Start feature gateway:**

```bash
cd backend/feature-gateway
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/online_judge \
cargo run
```

**4. Start frontend development server:**

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

**5. Start judge worker (optional, requires Linux environment):**

```bash
cd backend/judge-worker
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/online_judge \
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379 \
API_URL=http://localhost:3000 \
WORKER_SECRET=dev-secret \
cargo run
```

### Quality Checks

```bash
# API compilation and test checks
cd backend
cargo check -p api
cargo test -p api --no-run
cargo check -p judge-worker
cargo test -p judge-worker --no-run
cargo check -p feature-gateway

# Frontend type checking and build
cd frontend
npm run typecheck --silent
npm run build --silent

# Frontend E2E tests
npx playwright test e2e/smoke.spec.ts
```

